Description: Handle sliver of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine buff. Rectangular stamp with herm symbol.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 173, 26. Name Philostephanos. From same die as Delos TD 5763 and Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ALEX CON.0254.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0981)
